        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 8 at 6:12PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 612 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking an outflow boundary ahead
of a cluster of thunderstorms along a line extending from near
Longview to 9 miles west of Elysian Fields to 7 miles southwest of
Greenwood to 6 miles southeast of Stonewall. Movement of the outflow
boundary was north at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Shreveport, Longview, Bossier City, Marshall, Hallsville, Haughton,
Greenwood, Blanchard, Waskom, Stonewall, Tatum, Deberry, Elysian
Fields, Eastwood, Woodlawn, Harleton, Karnack, Fosters, Scottsville,
and Keachi.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
